Description: Home Elephant provides a social media application that connects neighbors and neighborhoods.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Atlanta Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Home Elephant connects neighbors and neighborhoods though our neighborhood social media application. Home Elephant was founded by a group of good people who realized they weren't great neighbors.  Home Elephant was founded because our neighborhoods have become barren wastelands of communication.  One of the founders has lived on the same street for 12 years and only knows 6 of his neighbors.  Another founder had an episode where his wife was assaulted while he was away on business, the police provided little help, and he wished there was a way to immediately alert his neighbors.  Another founder is a part of an HOA where they get their communication via email with no chronological view of the alerts.  They all agreed there must be a better way. Home Elephant, an Atlanta-based startup, takes neighborhood watch, event organization and the re-establishment of community into the 21st century.  HomeElephant can be accessed via the web, through their Facebook app, and through mobile devices.  The application utilizes Google map views to allow quick and easy viewing and posting of neighborhood communications.  Everything from crime alerts to garage sale notices can be easily posted and accessed by participating neighbors. www.homeelephant.com
Founders: Bonneau Ansley, Chandler Powell, Jeff Jahn, Matt Fromm

Description: Groqit sells a unique Personal Inventory Management System for collectors aimed at eliminating duplicate purchases.
Headquarters Regions: West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Groqit sells a unique Personal Inventory Management System for collectors aimed at eliminating duplicate purchases. The Groqit system consists of two parts:  the Groqit portable inventory computer and the groqit.com site services.  The Groqit device is the smallest, least expensive portable barcode reader available.  It has a built-in contact barcode reader and can read, store and search inventories.  A 2-line display provides visual confirmation of a scanned barcode and allows the user to read related information that is stored on the flash drive. The site services include translation of barcodes into human-readable information. The user's inventory is stored three ways: in the online database, as a backup file online and as searchable files on the Groqit. The complete system allows easy inventorying of collected items (DVDs, books, etc.), secure storage online, and while shopping, a fast, simple way to avoid buying duplicate items. The Groqit device is designed for simple interfacing to inventory systems via flat files on the USB drive.

A dramatic example is when the patient has a co-occuring diagnosis of depression, which affects an estimated 20% of those being treated for a chronic condition. As the chart on the left shows, this increases overall care utilization significantly, with an average of $4800 in excess annual expenses per patient. Make sure your patients feel heard, and they will reward you with better self-care. Research has shown Americans are adopting smartphones at a rapid pace. However, such device ownership is still below half of the total population. Would you invest in any medical offering that only served half of its potential users? Using the RxApps service, not only can you can reach smarthphone users with mobile web, you can reach almost any patient using modes of interaction with which they are already familiar: text messages and web applications. Description: ParaView is an open-source, multi-platform data analysis and visualization application.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: ParaView is an open-source, multi-platform data analysis and visualization application. It allows users to quickly build visualizations to analyze their data using qualitative and quantitative techniques. The data exploration can be done interactively in 3D or programmatically using ParaView’s batch processing capabilities. ParaView was developed to analyze extremely large datasets using distributed memory computing resources. It can be run on supercomputers to analyze datasets of petascale size as well as on laptops for smaller data, has become an integral tool in many national laboratories, universities and industry, and has won several awards related to high performance computation.
